deconvolution.algorithm

Class Controller

  • java.lang.Object
    • deconvolution.algorithm.Controller

  • public class Controller
extends java.lang.Object
    This is an important class to manage all the common task of the algorithm. The method start() is called before at the starting of the algorithm. The method ends() is called at the end of every iterations for the iterative algorithm. It returns true if one the stopping criteria is true. The method finish() is called when the algorithm is completely terminated. A timer is started to get the peak memory.
    Author:
    Daniel Sage
